description: For sale: $275,000. Year round home on White Iron Lake in Ely MN on 9 acres and 360+ feet of shoreline!  3 Bedroom/2.75 bath modified A frame home with amazing views. Outdoor entertainment will consist of a pool and massive deck space.   Detached  3 stall garage and an additional 36x36 metal pole building.  Fixer upper - but what an opportunity!

description: For sale: $169,000. Large A-Frame Home with a permanent dock space on Moose Lake!  Direct water access to the Moose Lake chain of lakes, and the Canadian border!  Home is aprox 1250 square feet, with a large living room, very nice kitchen, full bath, and bedroom on the main floor, and 2 more bedrooms and a 3/4 bath on the second floor.  2 large decks-one on each level, offer great views of the wooded paradise that surrounds the home.  Awesome creek with rapids flows year around just 75 feet from the home and offers soothing babbling brook sounds!  Just a couple of minute walk takes you to your dock located on the shore of Moose Lake, where you can keep your boat or canoe all summer long, and use for exploring this unique wilderness chain of lakes!  This property is surrounded by aprox 9 acres of mostly vacant association land that makes the setting very private.  There is also a 12' x 20' garage located a few hundred feet away.  Drilled well, private septic mound system.  Use as your up north cabin, or live here year around!

description: For sale: $119,900. Voyageur log cabin on ten acres of mostly high ground with good tree cover. Remote wilderness location with 2 miles of gravel forest road access that is nice to have a little higher clearance vehicle to get there.  About a half mile of the access road becomes a snowmobile trail in the winter. Property is surrounded by thousands of acres of State and Federal land. Land is connected to many miles of trails ideal for snowmobiling, skiing, hiking, and ATV-ing, as well as great hunting opportunities. Property is only 2 1/2 miles from the Farm Lake public boat launch and entry point into the BWCAW. Cabin is 24 X24 with a half loft sleeping area. Functioning kitchen has propane appliances. Bathroom has a low maintenance composting toilet, vanity, and shower stall.  All water drains are set up under the "bucket in, bucket out' rule from Lake County, MN.  There is presently no well here, so water is brought in by the owner. Propane lights thru out cabin. Power is supplied by solar panel and generator. Outbuildings include storage area and outhouse. Owner would consider financing with a qualified buyer.

description: For sale: $799,000. Stunning south facing dream home on a pine and granite studded lot just below Silver Rapids on Farm Lake. First time on the market, this well designed ultra modern home sits well above the lake to give you excellent 180 degree tranquill views of the lake. The home was well designed to allow an abundance of natural light throughout the living space. The main floor is absolutely stunning with the rock wall fireplace, oven, open dining and kitchen area done with a wall of windows to allow for the beauty of nature to combine with the comforts of home. On the lower level, there is a 3 car garage with entry to the large workshop or tiled spacious mudroom. The foyer entry has an elevator serving all the 3 levels. Adjacent to the mudroom, you will find a rec room complete with wet bar, an exercise room along with the utlility room and 3/4 bath. Taking the steps to the main level will find you on a beautiful natural light living space complete with rockwall fireplace, which is part of an open design great room. The spacious kitchen and dining area will never be a dull spot with the natural views of the Norhtwoods Lake and woods setting. The dining room is a special area with a hexagonal designed flooring. Above the Great Room and Master Bedroom, the Celestory windows allow for an abundance natural light.  There is a dock with boatlift just steps away from the home. description: For sale: $2,999,000. Take a step back in time to a bygone era and appreciate the finer things life had to offer back then in this beautifully maintained Showpiece Estate. Twinflower, aptly named by the founder for the abundance of Twinflowers on the property, is on one of the most coveted locations on Burntside. Not only due to it's location and historical value, but also by offering over 143 acres of property, two islands, and shoreline on TWO lakes. The stately 4 BR/3BA main home, two guest homes, and a rustic native field stone cabin on the 8.8 acre island are all tucked away for the utmost of privacy. The Burntside Lake side offers 7000 feet of sandy beach shoreline with North facing views and on Little Long side you have the opportunity of 1600 feet of South facing views! This property consist of 5 separate parcels. Twinflower will bring you back to the day of understate elegance. Featuring 4 bedrooms and 3 baths, formal dining room with it's own stone faced fireplace and French doors leading to the living room. There you can cozy up to another field-stone fireplace and gaze out over the water and watch the spectacular sunsets that Burntside is known and appreciated for. Two bedrooms on the main floor and two more bedrooms on the upper floor via a open staircase that emanates rustic elegance. Two boat houses, one with sleeping quarters take advantage of the lake breezes and tranquil night sounds. The two guest cabins are both 1 br cabins, also with field stone fireplaces, kitchenettes and bathrooms. There is no other opportunity like this in the area, let alone on these Lakes. This is a wonderful opportunity to create you own family legacy for generations to come, or even a corporate retreat, or private rentals. One of the Best!

description: For sale: $650,000. Retreat to this once in a lifetime property offering as it comes on the market for the very first time.  This is one rare opportunity to own a beautiful private wooded acreage on the North Arm of Burntside Lake with 248 feet of prime private lakeshore.  The new addition was incorporated in 2014 to an existing old world charm log cabin that occupied the Lindskog Resort Property since the early 1960's. The log building was completed in 1960. The logs are Montana lodge pole pine, shipped in from Montana just for the construction of this building.  The deck overlooks the North Arm of Burntside with a southeast big water view. The lot is mature tree covered and offers elevated views of the lake and bay. The new addition three bedroom home was well planned with an abundance of natural light and beautiful lake views. Along with the tremendous lake views, the home is offered with some original stained glass art windows, all Marvin windows, a new furnace and Duel fuel heating system, a lake water filtration system with heat tape, plumbing, back up generator, an all metal roof with insulation, new cabinetry, an LP fireplace, and a spray foam insulated basement along with a new septic are just some of the updates. description: For sale: $1,250,000. Stunning Burntside property with over 16 acres of pine-laden land and 1500 feet of pristine sand beach. The property is meticulously cared for and features a Huisman built Timber frame cottage, heated garage with upstairs office, and lakeside boathouse.  Finished with cedar lap siding and cedar shakes fitting in quietly to the natural surroundings. The west-facing home is filled with huge windows capturing the beauty of the surrounding lake, woods, and sunsets; bringing the Northwoods inside.  The main level features an open living area, with a contemporary kitchen, dining area, sitting room, laundry area, master bedroom and 3/4 bath, and generous entry area.  Off of the dining are patio doors leading to the lakeside stone patio area.  This year round home is evenly heated with zoned, dual-fuel in-floor heat.  There is a natural fieldstone framed fireplace, a true characteristic of our Northwoods.  Upstairs is a second bedroom and 3/4 bath, both bedrooms have beautiful west facing lake views overlooking Burntside Lake.  There is ample land to build a larger home on the property if desired.  Landscaped with beautiful perennial gardens, stone patio, and walkways, within a diverse forest including huge red and white pines.  The beautiful ledge rock ridge provides an amazing natural buffer, creating an incredibly private and peaceful setting.  Make this your lake place escape for recreating and quiet leisure.

description: For sale: $274,900. If the hustle and bustle of city life is getting you down maybe you need to take a look at this special getaway property. NOW OFFERING A $25,000 CREDIT FOR CONSTRUCTION OR RENOVATION.  ALSO POTENTIAL OWNER FINANCING. Nestled among the hills of the Moose Lake Entry Point, this comfortable 3 level studio home offers relaxation and inspiration as it overlooks the wilderness area of the Superior National Forest's BWCA. The open design of the main entry welcomes you into a world of natural light and beautifully incorporated wood paneling. The L shaped 8 x 50 foot deck extends the outdoor enjoyment space of main floor living. Just off the foyer, a main floor bedroom with deck offers a full wilderness view along with a deck side electric sauna for those relaxing evenings. All the staircase railings are of local log craftsmanship. Following the staircase to the second floor, you walk into the dining, kitchen and living room area. You immediately are surrounded by a wall of natural light and your eyes are drawn to the beauty of Moose Lake and the Boundary Waters just a short distance away. The view is spectacular, this one of a kind property that offers this on a daily basis. The kitchen area gives way to the Three season porch to add to your relaxing and creative pleasure.  All the staircase railings are of beautiful handmade local log craftsmanship. Working your way to the 3rd floor loft area, the view even gets better. This comfortable area is private and a great place to gather one's thoughts. There is a small deck off the loft which overlooks the garage and parking area and the government land to the south.  The garage footprint is a large 24 x 48. There are three stalls that measure 24 x 26 and extra stall measuring 10 x 24. On the main floor is an office at 12 x 14. A break room measuring 10 x 12 completes the main floor footprint. The upper level offers 3 extra rooms with a ¾ bath. This property would lend well to a small outfitting business as the main Moose Lake Entry point is just a ½ mile away. The property is protected by a standby propane 14 K automatic generator, a safety net in any weather. One has to imagine the possibilities this property offers. The privacy, the views of nature at it's best and of course, a place to unwind and relax. description: For sale: $224,900. Enjoy easy access to this well-kept, charming cabin on the shores of White Iron Lake. This updated A-Frame; offers 2 bedrooms and one bath.  A newer addition provides both master bedroom and a three-season porch where you can relax in comfort and enjoy scenic views of the lake.  A friendly main level living space provides master bedroom, spare bedroom, full bath, eat-in kitchen, and a living room with lake and wildlife views.  Recent updates include new carpeting, bathroom, septic system (2017), well, newer shingled roof, fresh stain on the cabin and shed.  A steel-sided garage along with the shed provide ample storage for recreational equipment and belongings. Minutes from Ely and located on a well-maintained road, the property gently slopes northwest toward the lake.  The cabin sits on +/- 1.07 acres and is surrounded by a clean and level grassy lawn which is then enveloped by mature birch and a mix of pines.  Enjoy a campfire by the shore as the sun sets.  The 173 feet of shoreline on this property is a mix of sand and rock. Depart from the dock and explore the White Iron Chain of Lakes.  In addition to White Iron, you can visit Farm Lake, Garden Lake, and South Farm; which is a BWCA entry point.  The White Iron chain and its 5200 acres is a Walleye fishery with a sizable Smallmouth Bass and Northern Pike population. At 3246 acres, White Iron provides for a wide range of water sports.  Make this playground your home away from home.

description: Recently sold: $375,000. description: Recently sold: $210,000. The setting is spectacular for this home/cabin on Fall Lake--with gorgeous views of Fall Lake in the front, and the beautiful sights and sounds of the rapids and falls of Lauder Creek as it tumbles into the lake outside your side window!  The home features an open floor plan with kitchen, dining area, and living room with wood burning fireplace, and full bath on the main floor, and a second bedroom, workshop, laundry room, and large unfinished room on the lower, walk-out level. There is also a historic log guest bunkhouse on the hill overlooking the lake, a 2 plus stall detached garage, and a large storage shed.  All this on approx. 1.6 acres with approx. 160 feet of shoreline on Fall Lake, and another 145 feet of shoreline on Lauder Creek.  The land is in a small bay on Fall Lake that has a shallow passageway into the main lake, which allows passage for small fishing boats and canoes/kayaks to the main lake--but is not deep enough for larger boats or pontoons. Fall Lake offers direct water access to the BWCAW--which is in the northern part of lake, and also access to Basswood Lake and the Canadian border!  You will love this wonderful home, property, and setting!

description: Recently sold: $457,000. Great privacy and seclusion at this 3 bedroom, 4 bath lake home on Wolf Lake approx. 7 miles west of Ely!  Over 11 acres of beautiful wooded land and approx. 225 feet of good hard sand/gravel swimming shoreline. Half-log sided home sits on a hill with wonderful lake views, and there is a nice little road to the lake and the dock.  Home features a large open floor plan living room, dining room, and kitchen with lots of cabinets and counter space on the main floor with a handy half bath.  Also, the master bedroom with master full bath AND a large fantastic 3 season porch, with adjoining deck!  Upstairs is a large loft room with open views of the main floor, a bedroom and 3/4 bath. The walk out lower level has a large family/rec room, another bedroom, a full bath, and the utility/laundry room.  Other features include central air, cathedral ceilings, a nice mix of gorgeous high quality native wood and drywall interior walls and ceilings, and great lake views throughout the house! Nice landscaping designed to keep lawn mowing to a minimum. Long, windy private driveway. Also, a new garage/workshop!  Wolf Lake is a quiet 288 acre lake that has very good fishing for bass, walleye, northern pike and panfish.  Peaceful and quiet are the key words here!!

Nice backyard is partially fenced. 2 stall detached garage.

description: Recently sold: $122,000. Large 3 bedroom / 2 bath home located on large corner lot. Large living room and dining room with refinished hardwood floors. description: Recently sold: $241,000. In city yet a country feel, unique 3-bedroom 1 3/4 bath home on 0.43 acres (six city lots) surrounded by mature pine trees. description: Recently sold: $465,000. Log home, located on Farm Lake in Ely, has everything you could possibly want in a lake home.  This beautiful 4 BR/2BA Lake  home sits on 3 acres of wooded land with 600 ft of lake shore frontage.  Sit back and enjoy a gorgeous view from your wrap around deck or your 3 season porch.  When you are inside this home, you can appreciate the spectacular view as well with all the windows.  The main level of this home has been completely renovated.  From the house there is a nice walking path that takes you down to the boathouse/bunkhouse and dock.  Enjoy a day of fishing on Farm Lake with the benefits being a part of the White Iron Chain of Lakes.  Farm Lake is connected to Garden Lake, South Farm Lake and White Iron Lake totaling around 11,000 acres of water.  Not to mention all of the activities Ely has to offer from its trails for biking, hiking and snowmobiling, you may also experience dog sledding, visiting the Dorothy Molter Museum, International Wolf Center or the beautiful views of the Kawishiwi Falls.  Ely also has many different restaurants and shopping to enjoy.  If you are looking for a Lake Home as a vacation retreat this may be the home for you.  This home has the potential to generate income.  It has already been approved by Ely Lodging and could be used as one of their rental properties during the times you are not planning to be at the property.  This home and view is truly a must to see.

description: Recently sold: $133,000. In town Dream! Make your appointment to see this one today!

description: Recently sold: $815,000. Custom built, red cedar log home on Eagles Nest Lake #3. This one owner home is located in the very private Swanson Shores area, adjacent to Bear Head State Park. Eagles Nest Lake #3 is one of Ely's hidden gems, with its crystal clear water, excellent fishing, and peaceful tranquility. Roughly 1/3 of the lake is encompassed by the aforementioned Bear Head State Park, ensuring the serene setting for now and the future. This property blends the experiences of lazy summer days at the  lake, with the cabin-in-the-woods front row seat to mother nature.

description: Recently sold: $165,000. Spacious 5 bedroom, 2 full bath home on the west side of Ely has approx 2600 sq. feet of comfortable living space!  This impressive 2 story home sits on a hill with great views of Ely and a distant view of Shagawa Lake and the ledge rock hills beyond! The main floor features a large living room with attached dining area, a spacious kitchen with lots of cabinet and counter space, main floor laundry, full bath, and a family room.  The 2nd floor has 5 large bedrooms, a full bath, and a bonus room for office or storage space. Large center hall serves the bedrooms on each side.  Other features include a total of 5 walk-in closets, huge 2 stall attached garage, maintenance free siding, large lot with big side yard, and a beautiful enclosed front porch to enjoy the view! Short walk to downtown shopping and the school.  Great home with plenty of space to grow into!!

Recently sold: $144,000. This property features phenomenal views of Moose Lake ? gateway to the Boundary Waters Canoe Area Wilderness. description: Recently sold: $124,000. First Snow.  Dogsledding, Skiing, Ice Fishing. Iconic Northern Minnesota Lake view from this nice 5 acre lot with gentle slope facing south west overlooking White Iron Lake.  Stay in this cute little Artist Cabin/Bunk House while you build your dream cabin or be satisfied with the simplicity of no well or septic.  The building site and cabin are aprox. 300ft from Lake with 100ft of Federal land between Lot and Lake. There is an outhouse and a 30 amp electric service.  I plan on adding a composting toilet and shower in the 6x8 bathroom and finishing the 8x9 bedroom.  There is also water collection from the roof for domestic use and a separate water collection for the sauna.  Check on my website for a few videos at cabindreamweaver.com.  Spend a weekend.  Take a sauna.  Go for a paddle or a ski on the lake. Call Wess Crawford - Wild Woods Land Company.  218-349-5340

description: Recently sold: $94,000. Well maintained 4 bedroom, 1.5 bath home located on a large corner lot. The lot is nicely landscaped with mature pines, lilacs, and flowers. Recently sold: $64,000. This home is immaculate. Two bedrooms on the first floor with additional space on the second. Home was originally a full two story home but was lowered. description: For sale: $122,900. description: Recently sold: $550,000. Custom Log Lake Home, Set In Pines On Private Gradual Lot, Beautiful Undeveloped Views, Just 9 Mi To Town! Set on 3.9 acres & 275 ft east-facing shoreline, West Robinson, a 120 acre lake in the Superior Natl Forest w/only 16 private homeowners on the lake. 3 fireplace Voyageur Log Home w/2 car garage & fully furnished private guest apt. Great rm w/wall of windows & gas firepl open to 80 ft lakefront deck. Huge gourmet kitchen w/island open to great rm & blue water vistas. Main flr lakeside master w/gas firepl, walk in closet, glass doors open to lakefront deck. Spacious loft w/water view offers family rm, full bth, another BR & guest apt. In-flr heat (incl garage), energy efficient wood & electric boiler, coverd entry, landscaped grounds w/lakeside firepit, abundant wildlife, nesting pair of rare Trumpeter Swans at dock.
